text:
Did anyone say that researching the rhetorical inimitability in the Holy Quran might imply that there is no inimitability except from this aspect? So we should not research the rhetoric of the Quran lest someone imagine that the Quran will not be miraculous unless we research its rhetoric? Rather, researching this science increases the believer in faith and certainty and refutes the claims of the people of disbelief and misguidance who claim that the Quran has no arrangement.

Al-Shawkani says, thinking that this science has no benefit: "How little is the benefit of such [a thing], how rare is its fruit, and how despicable is its utility. Rather, for one who understands what he says and what is said to him, it is a waste of times and spending of hours in a matter that returns no benefit to its doer nor to the one who stands upon it from the people." (1)

I say: This science has immense benefits. Through it, a face of the faces of Quranic inimitability, a characteristic of its characteristics, and the wisdom of its arrangement become clear to us. We also use it to reflect upon the speech of Allah Almighty and study it, understand its meanings and purposes, and other benefits which we will talk about in their place, God willing. It is part of reflecting upon the speech of Allah Almighty, and through it we extract lessons and sermons and recognize the purposes of Surahs and verses. Allah Almighty has commanded us to reflect upon His Noble Book. He said: {Then do they not reflect upon the Qur'an? If it had been from [any] other than Allah, they would have found within it much contradiction {82}} And He, Glory be to Him, said: {[This is] a blessed Book which We have revealed to you, [O Muhammad], that they might reflect upon its verses and that those of understanding would be reminded {29}}

A table filled and teeming, and gardens of joy, fresh, flowering, lush, fruitful, pleasing the looking eyes. Their branches intertwined, their flowers embraced, their birds harmonized, their fruits resembled each other, their streams mixed, their pearls were ordered, and their jewels were consistent in a regular necklace:
*Like pearls increasing in beauty when strung... And not decreasing in value when unstrung.*
Allah Almighty said in Surah Al-Isra: {And We have certainly diversified [the verses] in this Qur'an that they might be reminded, but it increases them in nothing but aversion. {41}}
And He Almighty said in Surah Ta-Ha: {And thus We have sent it down as an Arabic Qur'an and have diversified therein the warnings that perhaps they will avoid [sin] or it would cause them remembrance. {113}}
And He, Glory be to Him, said in Surah Al-Furqan explaining the wisdom of revealing the Quran piecemeal: {And those who disbelieve say, "Why was the Qur'an not revealed to him all at once?" Thus [it is] that We may strengthen thereby your heart. And We have recited it with distinct recitation. {32}}
So the coming of the Quran piecemeal over twenty-three years according to what incidents and occurrences necessitate, what suits circumstances and conditions, and what keeps pace with the stages the Da'wah passed through, then its arrangement according to what exists in the Preserved Tablet with this wisdom and splendor: is a characteristic of the characteristics of this Quran, and a feature of its features by which it was unique among previous books which were revealed all at once...

