text:
**Thematic Unity of a Single Verse:**
The face of interconnection between the parts of a single verse might not appear clear. Of that is the face of interconnection in His saying Almighty {They ask you, [O Muhammad], about the new moons. Say, "They are measurements of time for the people and for Hajj." And it is not righteousness to enter houses from the back, but righteousness is [in] one who fears Allah. And enter houses from their doors. And fear Allah that you may succeed. {189}}
In this case, the matter requires reflection and depth in understanding the noble verse. The question is about new moons, and the answer is: they are measurements of time for people and Hajj. But what is the connection of that to His saying Almighty {And it is not righteousness to enter houses from the back, but righteousness is [in] one who fears Allah. And enter houses from their doors. And fear Allah that you may succeed {189}}?

* In his interpretation of His saying Almighty in Surah At-Tur {And they will approach one another, inquiring of each other. {25} They will say, "Indeed, we were previously among our people fearful [of displeasing Allah]. {26} So Allah conferred favor upon us and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire. {27} Indeed, we used to supplicate Him before. Indeed, it is He who is the Beneficent, the Merciful." {28}} in the context of talking about the conditions of the people of Paradise: Al-Shawkani says: [And they will approach one another, inquiring of each other, meaning some of them asking others in Paradise about their condition and what they were in of worldly fatigue and fear of the outcome. So they praise Allah who removed from them sadness, fear, and worry, and what they were in of toil and distress in seeking livelihood and obtaining what is necessary of provision. It was said some say to others: 'By what did you reach this high rank?' It was said the questioning is between them at the Resurrection from graves. But the first is more likely due to the indication of the context that they have become in Paradise.] (1)
In his interpretation of Surah Al-Rahman, which was driven to clarify numerous favors of Allah Almighty upon the two weighty kinds (Jinn and Mankind), Al-Shawkani explains the aspect of favor in some verses. For the favors of Allah Almighty are apparent and hidden, and hidden favors need contemplation and thought until we realize the aspect of their being favors. Thus the aspects of interconnection between the verses driven to enumerate favors become clear to us:
* Of that is what he cited regarding the aspect of annihilation being of the favors of the Most Merciful. He Almighty said {Everyone upon it will perish. {26} And there will remain the Face of your Lord, Owner of Majesty and Honor. {27} So which of the favors of your Lord would you deny? {28}}
